name: Hamilton Enhanced Canadian Financials ETF
longDescription: The investment objective of HFIN is to replicate, to the extent reasonably possible and before the deduction of fees and expenses, a multiple of the performance of a rules-based, equal-weighted Canadian financial index HFIN will seek to achieve its investment objective by borrowing cash to invest in and hold a proportionate share of, or a sampling of the constituent securities of, the Solactive Canadian Financials Equal-Weight Index in order to track approximately 1.25x the performance of such Index. As an alternative to, or in conjunction with investing in and holding the constituent securities, HFIN may also invest in other securities, including Other Funds (as defined herein) to obtain exposure to the constituent securities of the Index in a manner that is consistent with HFINs investment objective. HFIN may also hold cash and cash equivalents or other money market instruments in order to meet its obligations.
